# Keybindings
# -----------
# The format is trigger=action.
#
# Trigger: +-separated list of keys and modifiers
#
# Valid modifiers are:
# - shift
# - ctrl (alias control)
# - alt (alias: opt, option)
# - super (alias: cmd, command).
#
# Use > to define a sequence (chord) of key presses.
# Sequences are not allowed for global: or all:-prefixed triggers.
#
# Action is the action to take when the trigger is satisfied.
# It takes the format prefix:action:param.
#
# Params are only valid if the action requires them.
# They are taken as-is, so quote the entire action if there are spaces.
#
# Valid prefixes are:
# - all - send the keybind action to all terminals.
# - global - The keybind is active globally, even when ghostty is not focused.
# - unconsumed - The keybind is passed through to the running program.
# - performable - The keybind is active only if the action can be performed in the current context.
#
# Valid actions are:
# - ignore - Do nothing, ignore the key input.
# - unbind - Remove the binding.
# - csi:text - Send a CSI sequence. e.g. csi:A sends "cursor up".
# - esc:text - Send an escape sequence. e.g. esc:d deletes to the end of the word to the right.
# - text:text - Send a string. Uses Zig string literal syntax. e.g. text:\x15 sends Ctrl-U.
# - any action that can be found using `ghostty +list-actions`.
#
